abstract: Analysts have begun to question whether Sweden’s financial system, and its regulators, are ready for a larger stage.
snippet: Analysts have begun to question whether Sweden’s financial system, and its regulators, are ready for a larger stage.
lead_paragraph: STOCKHOLM, Oct. 11 — As Sweden’s markets have gained the attention of international investors, analysts have begun to question whether the country’s financial system, and its regulators, are ready for a larger stage.

headline.main: Scandal May Hurt Sweden’s Desire for Bigger Role on Financial Stage
headline.print_headline: Scandal May Hurt Sweden’s Desire for Bigger Role on Financial Stage
